%S A394326 1,2,1,1,3,5,6,7,15,27,39,57,97,161,257,405,659,1076,1734,2784,4504,
%T A394326 7304,11813,19079,30854,49947,80802,130671,211376,342035,553403,
%U A394326 895296,1448462,2343628,3791970,6135218,9926549,16061178,25987091,42047032
%N A394326 Total number of connected defect cluster types of weight n in the span-stratified cluster expansion for the row-word inversion statistic on standard Young tableaux of shape (m,m,m).
%C A394326 Connected defect clusters arise from the hard-rod recursion Z(N;q) = Z(N-1;q) + Sum_{w,s} c(w,s)*q^w*Z(N-s;q), where c(w,s) is the number of connected cluster types of weight w and span s. The present sequence is a(n) = Sum_{s>=1} c(n,s).
%C A394326 The Fibonacci residual |a(n) - a(n-1) - a(n-2)|/a(n) < 0.0002 for n >= 30, confirmed by Hankel determinant analysis showing 2-state asymptotic dynamics.
%H A394326 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A394326/b394326.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100</a>
%H A394326 Morten Brydensholt, <a href="/A394326/a394326.py.txt">Python program</a>
%F A394326 a(n) ~ A * phi^n where phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2, verified to 4 significant figures for n = 30..40.
%F A394326 a(n) ~ a(n-1) + a(n-2) for large n (empirical).
%e A394326 a(1) = 1: one cluster type (single defect at span 1).
%e A394326 a(5) = 3: three cluster types, all at span 2.
%e A394326 a(7) = 6: five types at span 3 plus one type at span 2.
%o A394326 (Python) # See Links
